<%
  @bodyclass = "homepage"
%>

<a id="knightfdn" class="imagelink" href="http://knightfoundation.org/"></a>

<img id="document_stack" alt="" src="/images/home/docs.png" />

<div id="container">

  <h1 id="tagline">
    <b>DocumentCloud</b> turns documents into data.
  </h1>

  <div id="search_box_wrapper" class="text_input search noselect">
    <div class="icon search_glyph"></div>
    <div class="search_inner">
      <input placeholder="Search thousands of public documents..." id="search_box" />
    </div>
    <div class="icon cancel_search" title="clear search"></div>
  </div>

  <h2 class="serif">
    DocumentCloud can help you <b>analyze</b> your primary source documents,<br /> <b>annotate</b> 
    highlights,
    and <b>publish</b> the material that supports your story.
  </h2>

  <div id="content">

    <div class="graf section">
      <div class="number one"></div>
      <h3><b>Analyze</b></h3>
      <h4 class="serif">Discover the people, places, organizations, and dates in your documents.</h4>
      <br />
      DocumentCloud runs every document you upload through
      <a href="http://www.opencalais.com/">OpenCalais</a>, giving you
      access to extensive information about the people, places and organizations
      mentioned in each. We find all the dates in a document, and plot them on
      a timeline for you. We&rsquo;ll even help you find related documents and
      reporting in our catalog.
    </div>

    <span class="photo">
      <img src="/images/home/entities.png" />
      <span class="caption serif">Listing each page that contains a reference to a specific organization.</span>
    </span>

    <div class="graf section">
      <div class="number two"></div>
      <h3><b>Annotate</b></h3>
      <h4 class="serif">Highlight what matters.</h4>
      <br />
      Annotate documents to highlight key passages. Use <b>private notes</b> to organize
      your own thoughts. Use <b>public notes</b> to compose annotations that will be part
      of your published reporting. Every annotation has a unique URL, so you can
      point readers right to the passage you want to highlight.
    </div>

    <div class="graf">
      When Memphis&rsquo; Commercial Appeal published
      <a href="http://www.commercialappeal.com/withers-exposed/">Ernest Withers: Exposed</a>, 
      an extensive investigation which revealed that the photographer responsible 
      for some of the most iconic photographs of the civil rights movement, 
      Ernest Withers, had also been working as an FBI  informant, they were able 
      to point readers right to 
      <a href="http://www.commercialappeal.com/withers-exposed/pages-from-foia-reveal-withers-as-informant/#document/p2/a2431">the passage</a>
      that revealed the identity of confidential informant <b>ME 338-R</b>.
    </div>
    
    <span class="photo bleed">
      <img src="/images/home/withers.png" />
      <span class="caption serif">Highlighting the sentence that reveals Withers&rsquo; informant number.</span>
    </span>

    <div class="graf section">
      <div class="number three"></div>
      <h3><b>Publish</b></h3>
      <h4 class="serif">Share source documents with your readers.</h4>
      <br />
      Everything you upload to DocumentCloud stays private until you're ready 
      to make it public, but once you decide to publish your primary source documents, 
      they join thousands of other documents in our<br /> <b>public catalog</b>.
      Use our <b>document viewer</b> to embed documents on your own website and
      introduce your audience to your story&rsquo;s paper trail.
    </div>

    <div class="graf">
      From our catalog, reporters and the public alike can find your documents 
      and follow links back to your original reporting. DocumentCloud contains 
      court filings, hearing transcripts, testimony, legislation, lab reports, 
      memos, meeting minutes, correspondence. See what's 
      <a href="/public">already in our catalog</a>. 
      Make your documents part of the cloud.
    </div>

  </div>

</div>
